HEADWORD: Incomprehensive
<hw>In*com`pre*hen"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not
comprehensive; not capable of including or of understanding; not
extensive; limited.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>In*com`pre*hen"sive*ly</wf>,
<pos>a.</pos> <au>Sir W. Hamilton.</au> --
<wf>In*com`pre*hen"sive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> <au>T.
Warton.</au></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incompressibility</ent>⟦br⟧
